<DOC><DOCNO> SJMN91-06318071 </DOCNO><ACCESS> 06318071 </ACCESS><LEADPARA>  Secretary of State James Baker told South Korea today that the United Statesviews the possibility of a nuclear arms race in the region as &quot;an urgentproblem&quot; that requires the political and diplomatic muscle of the majorpowers. At the same time, Baker sought to allay concerns of the Seoulgovernment that he was proposing that the United States, Japan, China and theSoviet Union would dictate a solution.  </LEADPARA><SECTION>  Front  </SECTION><HEADLINE>  KOREANS WARNED OF NUCLEAR ARMS RACE  </HEADLINE><MEMO>  Foreign News in Brief  </MEMO><BYLINE>  Mercury News Wire Services  </BYLINE><COUNTRY>  USA  </COUNTRY><EDITION>  Stock Final  </EDITION><CODE>  SJ  </CODE><NAME>  San Jose Mercury News  </NAME><PUBDATE>   911113  </PUBDATE> <DAY>  Wednesday  </DAY><MONTH>  November  </MONTH><PG.COL>  5A  </PG.COL><PUBYEAR>  1991  </PUBYEAR><REGION>  WEST  </REGION><STATE>  CA  </STATE><WORD.CT>  74  </WORD.CT><DATELINE>  Wednesday, November 13, 199100318071,SJ1  </DATELINE><COPYRGHT>  Copyright 1991, San Jose Mercury News  </COPYRGHT><LIMLEN>  1  </LIMLEN><LANGUAGE>  ENG  </LANGUAGE></DOC>